snippet.textDisplay: Why can nobody understand that he is the "best" RB in the world because he started out as a midfielder and because his crossing is so good. He isn't the best at defending and isn't the best out and out RB but he is unlike every other RB in the world because his crossing ability is unrivalled. I just think it's unfair on other RBs that we're calling him the best when other RBs aren't trained to develop their crossing and attacking positioning to this standard. The best RB in the world should be a rock solid defender that can bring stability to his position regardless of which club he plays for. If trent plays for Southampton he is no longer the best RB in the world because he is not a rock solid defender. He would still have his crossing ability and attacking mindset but that wouldn't be what Southampton needs. He would just be another Masuaku (great technically and skill wise but average defender at best). Basically my point is Trent isn't the best defender because he isn't complete enough. There's an argument for him being one of, if not the best, crossers on the planet but not RB.
snippet.textOriginal: Why can nobody understand that he is the "best" RB in the world *because* he started out as a midfielder and *because* his crossing is so good. He *isn't* the best at defending and *isn't* the best out and out RB but he is unlike every other RB in the world because his crossing ability is unrivalled. I just think it's unfair on other RBs that we're calling him the best when other RBs aren't trained to develop their crossing and attacking positioning to this standard. The best RB in the world should be a rock solid defender that can bring stability to his position regardless of which club he plays for. If trent plays for Southampton he is no longer the best RB in the world because he is not a rock solid defender. He would still have his crossing ability and attacking mindset but that wouldn't be what Southampton needs. He would just be another Masuaku (great technically and skill wise but average defender at best). Basically my point is Trent isn't the best defender because he isn't complete enough. There's an argument for him being one of, if not the best, crossers on the planet but not RB.
